items.title: Gardy, Yanks back CC, pad WC lead vs. Twins
items.summary: CC Sabathia recovered from a shaky first inning to provide six solid frames and Brett Gardner drove in a pair of runs on Tuesday evening, leading the Yankees to a 5-2 victory over the Twins in another meeting of the top clubs in the American League Wild Card hunt.

items.title: Source: Blue Jays close to extending Estrada
items.summary: The Blue Jays are close to agreeing with Marco Estrada on a contract extension, a source told MLB.com's Jon Morosi on Tuesday night. The club has not confirmed the report.

items.title: Kang ready to put past to rest, get back to ball
items.summary: After a year away from professional baseball, Jung Ho Kang is ready to play again. In an interview with the Yonhap News Agency published Tuesday, Kang apologized for the drunken-driving arrest that has kept him out of the United States this season and looked forward to his time in the Dominican Winter League.

items.title: Altuve earns Lou Gehrig Memorial Award
items.summary: Jose Altuve was presented with the Lou Gehrig Memorial Award prior to Tuesday's game against the White Sox at Minute Maid Park. The award is presented annually to a Major Leaguer who best exemplifies the giving character of the Hall of Famer for whom it is named.
